   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Patch = suck.</span><hr size=1> I was there but I wasn't pissed from the crash because I was freezing once every 3 min it seemed.. When Verant adds in new stuff there is bound to be problems in the beginning.. Thats how all software works.  Most games have development cycles of years not only because of the time it takes to develop the game and stuff but also to stamp out major bugs..   Verant however has a team constantly thinking up new ideas that need to be implimented relatively quickly with No real beta.. Test server really isnt a true test server because it is unpaided people testing out new features and they hardly care if something works.<br>
<br>
If there is a problem I know verant will fix it right away. Probably even the next day.. Name other companies who do that?  The people who work for Verant are only human and they will make mistakes.  Whether you believe it or not Everquest is a very solid game and is very reliable for the cost you are paying.  Its virtually up all day every day and if there is a problem it had never taken more than 1 day to get the majority of people up and running.<br>
<br>
I applaud verant for keeping the servers so stable over the years even in the early years when good technology wasn't available.<br>
<br>
Asking the servers to go uninterrupted without problems forever is completely unreasonible for what they are doing..<br>
<br>
Most people pay 50 dollars a month for Cable TV which is much easier to set up than supporting an on-line game and you get more entertainment out of everquest anyway.<br>
<br>
<br>
I guess I am a bit more understanding to things going wrong than other people.  As long as the servers don't crash once a week I am happy. <p><center>
